text: John Skinner (by 1509 – 16 November 1571), of Reigate, Surrey, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Reigate in 1542 and for Surrey in 1555 and 1558. ==References== Category:1571 deaths Category:Year of birth uncertain Category:English MPs 1542–1544 Category:English MPs 1555 Category:English MPs 1558 Category:People from Reigate
